## HTML Conventions

### Semantic HTML
- Use semantic HTML5 elements (`<header>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<article>`, `<footer>`)
- Use proper heading hierarchy (h1 → h2 → h3)
- Add ARIA labels for icon-only buttons and complex components
- Include alt text for all images

### URL Structure & Paths
- **Clean URLs**: All internal page links use clean URLs without `.html` extensions (e.g., `/about`, `/contact`, `/services`)
  - Old `.html` URLs automatically redirect to clean URLs via `.htaccess` (301 redirect)
  - Homepage: `/` (not `/index.html`)
- **Absolute Paths**: All resource paths (CSS, JS, images) must use absolute paths starting with `/`
  - ✅ Correct: `href="/css/style.css"`, `src="/js/main.js"`, `src="/assets/images/logo.webp"`
  - ❌ Incorrect: `href="css/style.css"`, `src="js/main.js"` (relative paths break on root URL)
  - **Why**: Ensures resources load correctly when accessing root URL (`/`) vs `/index.html`
- **Internal Links**: Use clean URLs for all internal navigation
  - ✅ Correct: `<a href="/about">`, `<a href="/contact#quote">`
  - ❌ Incorrect: `<a href="about.html">`, `<a href="/about.html">`
- **URL Rewriting**: `.htaccess` handles URL rewriting and redirects
  - Clean URLs (`/about`) internally serve from `about.html`
  - Old `.html` URLs redirect to clean URLs (301 permanent redirect)
  - Works for both production and development environments

### Component Loading
```html
<!-- Component placeholders -->
<div id="navbar-placeholder"></div>
<div id="breadcrumb-placeholder"></div> <!-- Optional: only on non-homepage pages -->
<div id="footer-placeholder"></div>

<!-- Scripts (in order) - Use absolute paths -->
<!-- Theme Manager - Load early to prevent FOUC -->
<script type="module" src="/js/utils/theme.js"></script>
<script type="module" src="/js/components.js"></script>
<script type="module" src="/js/alpine-setup.js"></script>
<script type="module" src="/js/main.js"></script>
